	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Now that you talked, I started to think a bit more. <br />It doesn't makes much sense to strip a well known board naked.<br />At least the well documented ones as this don't!<br /><br />Other than curiosity there's no more valuable information to be gained from these.<br />But on pirate or unknown boards it does! <br />Specially if you don't want to miss any connection, wich is possible if you're with an exotic board and don't test all the possibilities.<br /><br />At least the game is working and I have a nice board.<br />Probably it's a mapper IC problem, but I'll never be sure if I don't try to make a repro with this board.

		

		</td>
